		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">More on Weapon Damage<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Aug 21st 7:15 PM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=99843573415301&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=99843573415301&num=5&page=&post=1&replyto=99843573415301"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=99843573415301></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=17094"><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>397 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Greetings fellow Paladins,<br><br>In an effort to help my fellow holy knights, as well as myself, I continue to delve into the different weapons, their damage, their speed factors, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;My latest research has taken me to the Copeland Weapon Analyzer.  What a great piece of software this is!<br><br>I went through and configured various "common" weapons looking at their "Damage/Minute" ratings (note...that is NOT Damage/Second...of course, divide by 60 and there you have it!).  What I found corroborated my earlier information...that being that the Mithril 2-hand sword is hard to beat without some type of non-weapon haste item to help you along, and even then, the Mithril beats several nice weapons. <br><br>Here's the information based on a 50th level Dwarven Paladin with maxed Weapon Skills of 200 and a Strength of 130! The Analyzer also uses the 60% hit rule for Paladins, which appears to be the universally accepted standard.<br><br>*Note: The Analyzer takes into account BASH damage for those weapons that are only 1-hs.<br><br>Mithril 2-hand Sword<br>Damage per Minute: 706<br><br>Wurmslayer<br>Damage per Minute: 544<br>Add bashing for 23 pts and you total: 567<br>(I realize you get an increase in AC with this weapon)<br><br>Arbitors Combine Greatsword<br>Damage per Minute: 669<br><br>Dwarven Sap<br>Damage per Minute: 493<br>Add bashing for 23 pts and you total: 516<br><br>Soulfire<br>Damage per Minute: 538<br><br>Now, I decided to add the most common Haste item out there and the one that everyone loves to dream about getting. That being the Flowing Black Silk Sash (FBSS).  I re-ran the numbers and here's what I came up with!<br><br>Mithril 2-hand Sword<br>Damage per Minute: 706<br>(The hastes do NOT stack according to Copeland)<br><br>Wurmslayer<br>Damage per Minute: 658<br>Add bashing for 29 pts and you total: 687<br>The Wurmslayer AND FBSS still do NOT beat the Mithril 2-hs, but you do get added AC from shield.<br><br>Arbitors Combine Greatsword<br>Damage per Minute: 810<br><br>Dwarven Sap<br>Damage per Minute: 597<br>Add bashing for 29 pts and you total: 626<br><br>Soulfire<br>Damage per Minute: 651<br><br>So, unless you have a non-weapon Haste Item, the Mithril 2-hand sword is pretty hard to beat! The Wurmslayer, a MOST popular item, continues to lag behind the Mithril 2-hand sword even WITH an FBSS!! If you need the added Armor Class of the shield and you need to Bash casters, etc. then the Wurmslayer may be the weapon you need. Otherwise it is too dang slow.<br><br>The Arbitor Combine Greatsword picks up nicely with the added haste from an FBSS.  I have used an Arbitors on several occasions, although I do not own one myself.  They hit HARD!  No doubt about it.  But, without a Haste item to help them along, they don't match up with the Mithril 2-hand sword.<br><br>There were several weapons that performed better, those mostly being the Etched and Exquisite Velium Battle Axes, WarLances, etc. that drop in Dragon Necropolis, and a few even more rare and difficult to obtain items. But for less than 2k plat, you can pick up a Mithril 2-hand sword and be close to even those weapons.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>50th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br><br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >5 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
